{"parentUuid":"f8075d46-badb-4b40-ba2b-192f1f5f7bba","isSidechain":false,"message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-7","id":"msg_01RFZpWFhuwe5hGgQQph8qRg","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_01HpMcZCEfimeKLfAFBWX3QJ","name":"Bash","input":{"command":"cat ~/.claude/frameworks/trellis/framework/phase2-contracts.md 2>&1","description":"Read Phase 2 contracts instructions"},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":"tool_use","stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":6,"cache_creation_input_tokens":37116,"cache_read_input_tokens":14909,"output_tokens":178,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":37116,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[{"input_tokens":6,"output_tokens":178,"cache_read_input_tokens":14909,"cache_creation_input_tokens":37116,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":37116},"type":"message"}],"speed":"standard"},"diagnostics":{"cache_miss_reason":{"type":"tools_changed","cache_missed_input_tokens":44987}}},"requestId":"req_011CadCwhfveK6bKgrYqdoDG","type":"assistant","uuid":"30081b07-1e00-4d33-813f-f7ffaf82ab05","timestamp":"2026-05-02T05:41:12.178Z","userType":"external","entrypoint":"cli","cwd":"/Users/avinkrism4pro/Personal/apps/MyApps/whatAmIDoing","sessionId":"72a03414-ba52-4106-b27a-7f28ae50fe45","version":"2.1.126","gitBranch":"main"}
{"parentUuid":"30081b07-1e00-4d33-813f-f7ffaf82ab05","isSidechain":false,"promptId":"32d6eb19-696f-4b7f-9376-049c28a357e2","type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01HpMcZCEfimeKLfAFBWX3QJ","type":"tool_result","content":"# Phase 2: Interface Contracts\n\n**Goal**: Generate a contract file for every component in `.framework/plan.md`. Contracts define exact interfaces before any building begins.\n\n## Why This Phase Matters\n\nWithout contracts, N components built in parallel produce N incompatible interfaces. The assembler spends more time adapting mismatches than it would have taken to build sequentially. Contracts are the make-or-break of this entire approach.\n\n## Process\n\n### Step 1: Setup\n\nCreate the contracts directory structure:\n\n```\n.framework/contracts/\n├── data/\n├── ui/\n├── logic/\n└── theme/\n```\n\n### Step 2: Generate Contracts\n\nRead ALL four contract templates in parallel:\n- `.framework/templates/contract-data.md`\n- `.framework/templates/contract-ui.md`\n- `.framework/templates/contract-logic.md`\n- `.framework/templates/contract-theme.md`\n\nThen generate contracts using sub-agents for speed. **Dispatch ALL layer agents in a single message for maximum parallelism** — L1 (data), L2 (UI), L3 (logic), and L4 (theme) contracts have no cross-dependencies at generation time, so they can all run concurrently.\n\n**Model assignment: Use `model: \"sonnet\"` for contract generation agents.** Contract generation is structured output from templates — Sonnet handles it well and is faster/cheaper than Opus. The orchestrator (Opus) handles the consistency review.\n\nEach agent receives in its prompt:\n- The contract template for its layer\n- The relevant Component Inventory YAML section from `.framework/plan.md`\n- The Tech Stack from `.framework/plan.md` (for type signatures)\n- The Screens section from `.framework/plan.md` (for context on how components are used)\n- Instructions to write each contract to `.framework/contracts/{layer}/{component_name}.contract.md`\n\n**Use the project's chosen language for all type signatures.** If `.framework/plan.md` says TypeScript, types are TypeScript. If Dart, types are Dart. Etc.\n\n**CRITICAL: Dispatch all layer agents in ONE tool-call message, not sequentially.** L1+L2+L3+L4 are independent.\n\n### Step 3: Cross-Contract Consistency Check\n\nAfter all agents complete, verify across all contracts. Use Grep to check systematically — do not just spot-check 2-3 types. **Use `model: \"haiku\"` for validation agents if delegating checks.**\n\nVerify:\n\n- [ ] Every input/output has an explicit type — no `dynamic`, `any`, `object`\n- [ ] Every method has a defined return type\n- [ ] Dependencies are listed explicitly — no implicit coupling\n- [ ] Edge cases are called out (empty lists, null values, zero states)\n- [ ] Naming is consistent across contracts (if `TaskId` is `String` in one contract, it's `String` everywhere)\n- [ ] No contract references implementation details of another contract — only interfaces\n- [ ] Types that cross contract boundaries match exactly (if a data store returns `List<Task>`, the logic component that consumes it expects `List<Task>`, not `Task[]`)\n\n### Step 4: User Review\n\nPresent contracts to the user for review. Key things to verify:\n\n- Are the API surfaces correct? (methods, props, callbacks)\n- Are edge cases covered?\n- Are there missing components that should have been identified in Phase 1?\n- Do the layer dependencies make sense?\n\nIterate until approved.\n\n### Step 5: Update Progress\n\nUpdate `.framework/progress.md`:\n- Set current phase to 2, status to complete\n- Add Phase 2 to history\n- Mark all components' Contract column as \"done\"\n\n## Completion Gate\n\n- [ ] Every component from `.framework/plan.md` has a contract file in `.framework/contracts/{layer}/`\n- [ ] All contracts pass the cross-contract consistency check\n- [ ] User has reviewed and approved all contracts\n- [ ] `.framework/progress.md` updated","is_error":false}]},"uuid":"51866002-3738-4496-a80d-f1d3411c16bc","timestamp":"2026-05-02T05:41:12.535Z","toolUseResult":{"stdout":"# Phase 2: Interface Contracts\n\n**Goal**: Generate a contract file for every component in `.framework/plan.md`. Contracts define exact interfaces before any building begins.\n\n## Why This Phase Matters\n\nWithout contracts, N components built in parallel produce N incompatible interfaces. The assembler spends more time adapting mismatches than it would have taken to build sequentially. Contracts are the make-or-break of this entire approach.\n\n## Process\n\n### Step 1: Setup\n\nCreate the contracts directory structure:\n\n```\n.framework/contracts/\n├── data/\n├── ui/\n├── logic/\n└── theme/\n```\n\n### Step 2: Generate Contracts\n\nRead ALL four contract templates in parallel:\n- `.framework/templates/contract-data.md`\n- `.framework/templates/contract-ui.md`\n- `.framework/templates/contract-logic.md`\n- `.framework/templates/contract-theme.md`\n\nThen generate contracts using sub-agents for speed. **Dispatch ALL layer agents in a single message for maximum parallelism** — L1 (data), L2 (UI), L3 (logic), and L4 (theme) contracts have no cross-dependencies at generation time, so they can all run concurrently.\n\n**Model assignment: Use `model: \"sonnet\"` for contract generation agents.** Contract generation is structured output from templates — Sonnet handles it well and is faster/cheaper than Opus. The orchestrator (Opus) handles the consistency review.\n\nEach agent receives in its prompt:\n- The contract template for its layer\n- The relevant Component Inventory YAML section from `.framework/plan.md`\n- The Tech Stack from `.framework/plan.md` (for type signatures)\n- The Screens section from `.framework/plan.md` (for context on how components are used)\n- Instructions to write each contract to `.framework/contracts/{layer}/{component_name}.contract.md`\n\n**Use the project's chosen language for all type signatures.** If `.framework/plan.md` says TypeScript, types are TypeScript. If Dart, types are Dart. Etc.\n\n**CRITICAL: Dispatch all layer agents in ONE tool-call message, not sequentially.** L1+L2+L3+L4 are independent.\n\n### Step 3: Cross-Contract Consistency Check\n\nAfter all agents complete, verify across all contracts. Use Grep to check systematically — do not just spot-check 2-3 types. **Use `model: \"haiku\"` for validation agents if delegating checks.**\n\nVerify:\n\n- [ ] Every input/output has an explicit type — no `dynamic`, `any`, `object`\n- [ ] Every method has a defined return type\n- [ ] Dependencies are listed explicitly — no implicit coupling\n- [ ] Edge cases are called out (empty lists, null values, zero states)\n- [ ] Naming is consistent across contracts (if `TaskId` is `String` in one contract, it's `String` everywhere)\n- [ ] No contract references implementation details of another contract — only interfaces\n- [ ] Types that cross contract boundaries match exactly (if a data store returns `List<Task>`, the logic component that consumes it expects `List<Task>`, not `Task[]`)\n\n### Step 4: User Review\n\nPresent contracts to the user for review. Key things to verify:\n\n- Are the API surfaces correct? (methods, props, callbacks)\n- Are edge cases covered?\n- Are there missing components that should have been identified in Phase 1?\n- Do the layer dependencies make sense?\n\nIterate until approved.\n\n### Step 5: Update Progress\n\nUpdate `.framework/progress.md`:\n- Set current phase to 2, status to complete\n- Add Phase 2 to history\n- Mark all components' Contract column as \"done\"\n\n## Completion Gate\n\n- [ ] Every component from `.framework/plan.md` has a contract file in `.framework/contracts/{layer}/`\n- [ ] All contracts pass the cross-contract consistency check\n- [ ] User has reviewed and approved all contracts\n- [ ] `.framework/progress.md` updated","stderr":"","interrupted":false,"isImage":false,"noOutputExpected":false},"sourceToolAssistantUUID":"30081b07-1e00-4d33-813f-f7ffaf82ab05","userType":"external","entrypoint":"cli","cwd":"/Users/avinkrism4pro/Personal/apps/MyApps/whatAmIDoing","sessionId":"72a03414-ba52-4106-b27a-7f28ae50fe45","version":"2.1.126","gitBranch":"main"}
