e, view/theme toggle}\n\n## Sizing / Layout\n\n{Describe page layout: max-width content column, sticky TOC sidebar on >=lg, stacked on mobile. Responsive breakpoints. Print-friendliness.}\n\n## Theme Dependency\n\n{Token names from DesignTokens contract that this component consumes — e.g., --waid-color-bg, --waid-color-fg, --waid-color-accent, --waid-font-body, --waid-font-mono, --waid-space-1..8, --waid-radius-md, --waid-shadow-card. Reference TOKENS, not raw values.}\n\n## Test Requirements\n\n- [ ] Renders correctly with full fixture analysis JSON\n- [ ] Handles edge values: empty sections, very long text, single-character glossary term\n- [ ] View toggle persists across reload (localStorage)\n- [ ] Theme toggle persists across reload (localStorage)\n- [ ] No XSS: HTML inside analysis text is escaped\n- [ ] Mermaid CDN failure does not break the page\n- [ ] Works offline if Mermaid is the only network dep\n```\n\n# Critical Requirements\n\n1. **HtmlTemplate** is a static `.html` file with placeholder tokens. Document EVERY placeholder using the format `__WAID_FOO__` and what gets substituted in.\n2. **InteractiveJS** is a single `.js` file embedded by the template. It must:\n   - Expose `window.WAID` with `init(analysisJson)` (idempotent), `setView('technical' | 'layman')`, `setTheme('light' | 'dark' | 'auto')`.\n   - Render JSON to DOM by template cloning (use `<template>` elements in the HTML), not innerHTML on user-content strings.\n   - Hydrate Mermaid only after the architecture section is rendered.\n   - Persist `waid-view` and `waid-theme` in localStorage.\n   - Initialize quiz state, evaluate answers locally, never network.\n3. Theme tokens listed must be consistent across both contracts (use the same names — keep a list).\n4. Be specific about DOM IDs / classes that the launcher or other components need to know about. For example: `#waid-root`, `#waid-toc`, `#waid-view-toggle`, `#waid-theme-toggle`, sections with `data-waid-section=\"overview\"`, etc.\n\